In re LILLIES OF THE FIELD, Inc. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. November 22, 1922.) No. 90. Charles E. Francis, of New York City (Arthur F. Driscoll and Joseph Walker Magrauth, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Max Roekmore, of New York City (David Haar, of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before ROGERS, HOUGH, and MAYER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed in open court.
